node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

node.text: Explore must-have  swimwear from @SculptSwim and find out why everyone is raving about them 🔥💕

🍑FULL BOOTY WORKOUT AT HOME🍑

I did something different today. Took my ankle weights(5lb)  then I set my timer ⏲️ on 1 minute and did all these workouts back to back for  1 minute on,  30 seconds off between each workout.
(If you are doing single leg, it's one minute per leg) 

I DID 4 REPS. 
AND LET ME TELL  YOU!! YOUR GLUTES ARE GOING TO BE ON FIRE 🔥😩🙌

PLEASE LIKE, COMMENT, SAVE, SHARE,  YOUR love means a lot. ❤❤
credit @body_by_clo

Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚

 How to fix hip thrust form in 30 seconds. Get those booty gains 💪🏻
cc: @dre.camp

BUDDY WORKOUT 👯‍♀️❤️‍🔥 TAG your babes and challenge them to workout together ⬇️👀 See you tomorrow at 8:00am EST for a booty and leg workout 🔥 Method: repeat each exercise 3 times - 45sec ON 10sec OFF

Save, share and let’s do it sis 👊🏼 

BUDDY WORKOUT 👯‍♀️❤️‍🔥 Etiqueta a tu pareja de entrenamiento y rétala para entrenar juntas ⬇️👀
Nos vemos mañana para entrenar piernas y glúteos a las 8:00am EST 🔥 
Method: repite cada ejercicio 3 veces- 45seg ON - 10seg OFF

Guarda la rutina, compártela y hagámosla juntas 👊🏼
-

Music: Cosa guapa by Rauw Alejandro
Credit @muscle_sisters #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚 

🤸🏻‍♀️Tips Sunday🤸🏻‍♀️
•••
Press Handstand Mobility
•••
Press handstands require a good amount of mobility, but also a good amount of compression strength. This means that not only do you need to be able to get into the position while stretching, but you need to be able to pull yourself into these positions while working.
•••
Here are a few of my go to drills!
•••
1.Wall Assisted Pike Stretch- partner assisted is always a plus!
2.Weighted Pancake Stretch- you can use a weight…or a toddler 😉
3.Weighted Dynamic Pancake Stretch- this one really helps build strength through the necessary range of motion!
4.Overhead Weighted Straddle Press- this one is a little more advanced and requires a good amount of shoulder mobility. Tip: go SLOW the first time you try this one…I fell on my head on my first try 🙈
5.Jefferson Curls- another great way to build strength through an extended range of motion!
6.Middle Split Roll Throughs- I’m not really sure what these are called…all I know is that I really struggle with them haha. If you can pull it off, it’s a cool way to stretch wall passing through the straddle press handstand movement pattern.
cc: @chels_mck
